  ---
  User Journeys

  Journey 1 — First use (onboarding)

  Register → Home (empty, no groups)
    → "Create your first group" CTA
    → Create Group sheet → "Flat 4B"
    → Group detail, Members tab
    → "Add your flatmates" prompt
    → Add Raj by email → Add Priya → Add Karan
    → Group is ready
    → Tap [＋] → Add first expense

  ---
  Journey 2 — Quick expense add (most common daily flow)

  Open app → Home
    → Tap [＋] FAB
    → Add Expense sheet opens (amount focused)
    → Type "1200"
    → Type "Groceries"
    → Category: 🛒 (tap)
    → Paid by: Mohak (already selected)
    → Participants: all 4 (already selected, equal split)
    → Shows "₹300 each"
    → Tap "Add Expense"
    → Toast: "Added"
    → Sheet closes, back on Home

  Total taps: ~6. Time: ~10 seconds.

  ---
  Journey 3 — Check who I owe

  Open app → Home
    → Balance card: "You owe ₹450 overall"
    → Tap "Flat 4B" group row
    → Group Detail → Balances tab
    → See: Raj — you owe ₹350
    →        Priya — owes you ₹200
    →        Karan — settled ✓
    → Simplified: "Pay Raj ₹350 to clear everything"

  ---
  Journey 4 — Settle up

  Group Balances tab
    → Raj row → tap "Settle up"
    → Sheet: "You → Raj, ₹350.00"
    → Optionally edit amount (partial)
    → Add note "GPay"
    → "Record payment"
    → Toast: "Recorded"
    → Balances refresh — Raj now shows "Settled ✓"

  ---
  Journey 5 — Unequal rent split

  Tap [＋] → Add Expense sheet
    → Amount: 32000
    → Description: "March Rent"
    → Category: 🏠
    → Paid by: Mohak
    → Expand "More options"
    → Split type → "Exact"
    → Mohak: 8000, Raj: 9000, Priya: 7500, Karan: 7500
    → Shows "₹32,000 — fully assigned ✓"
    → "Add Expense"

  ---
  Journey 6 — Two-person expense (just Mohak & Raj)

  Tap [＋] → Add Expense sheet
    → Amount: 800 (dinner)
    → Description: "Dinner, Bandra"
    → Category: 🍕
    → Paid by: Mohak
    → Participants: deselect Priya and Karan (tap to toggle off)
    → Shows "₹400 each"
    → Add

  ---
  Journey 7 — View expense history / find something

  Groups tab → Flat 4B → Expenses tab
    → Scroll through list, sorted by date
    → Grouped by month
    → Tap an expense → Expense Detail
    → See full split, who owes what

  ---
  Journey 8 — Someone added me to a group (new invite flow)

  New user gets invited via email → they register
    → They're already in the group (added by admin)
    → Home shows "Flat 4B" with a balance
    → They can start adding expenses immediately

  (Note: The API adds by email — the person needs an account first. The UX
  expectation: "make your account, I'll add you.")

  ---
  Key Design Decisions

  1. Amount input — large, first, focused

  The amount field is the first thing that appears and should be auto-focused.
   On mobile this means the number keyboard comes up immediately. Large
  display font (hero size) so you can see what you're typing.

  2. All group members selected by default

  In a 4-person flat, 90% of expenses involve all 4. Default to all-selected,
  tap to deselect individuals. Faster than selecting one-by-one.

  3. Equal split is the default

  Most expenses are equal. Other split types hidden under "More options".
  Equal shows the per-person amount live as you type the total.

  4. No group selection step from group context

  If you're inside a group and tap [＋], skip the group picker. If from Home,
  show a group picker at the top of the add sheet.

  5. Balance direction language

  Always state direction explicitly: "You owe Raj ₹350" (not just "₹350 with
  Raj"). Positive/negative sign conventions confuse people — plain English
  doesn't.

  6. Settle Up pre-fills the correct amount

  "Settle up" from a person row pre-fills the net simplified amount. User can
  lower it for partial settlement. Never pre-fill more than owed.

  7. Sheet pattern for creation flows

  Add Expense, Settle Up, Create Group, Add Member — all bottom sheets. Keeps
  context. No deep navigation stack for common actions.

